Description: Lower body sherd of Aeolian Wild Goat Style pottery dinos; white slip; interior black; exterior, from top: lower oart of frieze of outlined tongues with faded added red; below, three bands and top of a similar frieze (or guilloche?) with short dotted spikes in the interstices.
Producer name: Attributed to: The London Dinos Group
Bibliographic references: Kerschner 2006 / On the Provenance of Aiolian Pottery (p.122 fig.4, Appendix 2 Nau13)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GK.11)
